<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n54109g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54109g">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54109g"> 109(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Muhajirin fugitives</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">There were many exiles from Meccah, who had fled from the persecutions of the Kuraysh; they were known as the <mark>Muhajirin or Refugees</mark>, while the citizen of Med&#299;nah, who were converts, were called Ansars, or Helpers. <small> Edith Holland, <a name="EHSM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EHSM"><cite title="source">The Story of Mohammed</cite></a> (1914) 91</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
